<TITLE> Saudi riyals worth Tk 1.5 crore seized at ZIA </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 25 (bdnews24.com)  Customs authorities have seized Saudi riyals worth about Tk 1.5 crore from two Singapore-bound passengers at Zia International Airport, police said Friday. Customs officials recovered the riyals from the two passengers after a luggage search while they were entering the airport Thursday night. Airport police detained Mukul Hasan, 25, of Solar Char in Munshiganj and Omar Faruq, 19, of Tamakpatty in Narayanganj. A case against the two was filed with the police Friday, sub-inspector Md Jamal told bdnews24.com. Jamal said the two men had arrived at ZIA at 9:30pm Thursday to fly to catch a Singapore Airlines flight. Customs officials searched their luggage on entry to the airport and recovered 810,500 Saudi riyals, equivalent to about Tk 1.5 crore. bdnews24.c
